title: yogitoes® yoga towel
description: Looking for ways to up your Down Dog game? The patented Skidless® technology in these yoga towels enhances grip as you move through your flow, and silicone nubs underneath the towel keep it in place on your mat, preventing slipping no matter how much you move or sweat. Bonus? They’re eco-friendly, made with 50% recycled polyester from plastic bottles. Happy Savasana.
bullet1: Patented Skidless® technology using 100% silicone nubs to grip the towel in place on your mat, floor, or carpet
bullet3: Lightweight and great for travel
bullet4: Made using recycled bottles requiring 66% less energy to produce
bullet5: All dyes are free of AZO, lead, and heavy metals
bullet6: To Use: Place yogitoes towel on top of the yoga mat, dot-side down. Depending on your preference, you can start with a dry towel, or slightly dampen the areas under the hands and feet before you begin. Avoid rolling up damp yogitoes with your mat, because it can breed bacteria.
bullet7: To Wash: Machine wash cold with like colors. Deeper colors may require separate washings to remove excess dye. Tumble dry low or hang to dry. Do not bleach. Do not use dryer sheets, fabric softeners or detergents with fabric softener.

title: Reebok Classic x Kendrick Lamar Club C
description:
Kendrick Lamar first pulled on a pair of Reeboks in middle school. He comes back to these shoes today for the community they remind him of. This Club C edition sports a simple, clean look while mixing in colors that evoke equality, passion, power, and strength.
Its acid-washed denim and dash heel elements accentuate the mysterious personality of the shoe. Its black and white pattern represents equality within society and coming together as one, while the red label and heel elements symbolize strength, power and passion heard in Kendrick's music and seen in his actions. Having the branding on the inside of the tongue tag forces people to think, inspect past the surface and ties in to the anonymity of the shoe. The highlighted "k" and "o" details in the quarter logo window, however, refers to Kendrick's nickname, "K Dot", to give the shoe an inconspicuous identity.

In this pack, the speckled-effect midsole amplifies the modern light footed cushioning that only today’s materials can add to such a classic shoe. The low-cut design offers freedom of motion while the mesh, ballistic nylon and nubuck upper lends durability and support. Although these features are what will keep you comfortable all day long, it’s the unmistakable design details that make this pack another go-to staple in the timeless Classic Leather collection.
color: Collegiate Navy / Smoky Indigo / Deep Cobalt
bullet1: Mesh, ballistic nylon, and nubuck upper for durable and comfortable support
bullet2: Low-cut design for freedom of motion and quicker foot stride transitions
bullet3: Precision-cut EVA midsole for ultra lighweight, cushy shock absorption
bullet4: Speckled effect midsole foam for a unique on-track style
bullet5: High abrasion rubber outsole for  road-worthy traction that lasts
bullet6: Perfed vamp for breathability and layered upper construction for hits of color
bullet7: Padded foam sockliner for added cushioning and up-to-date comfort

title: Reebok CrossFit Nano 7
description: Introducing the latest addition to your gym bag: the Nano 7. This next generation of our CrossFit shoe keeps the natural shape and stability athletes covet, and comes with a flexible bottom for mobility and traction. The added heel piece creates a fit lockdown for better leverage as you lift.
bullet1: NanoWeave technology on the upper for comfort and breathability
bullet2: Anatomical toe box and a low-cut design for a natural feel and ankle mobility
bullet3: Ortholite sockliner for cushion
bullet4: 360-degree TPU heel wrap for a locked-in feel
bullet5: Crystallized rubber outsole flexes naturally for balance and stability
bullet6: 4mm heel-to-toe drop

title: Reebok CrossFit Speed TR
description: Always be ready for your next rep. All-direction stability keeps your base of support solid, helping you exert maximum power and reach top speeds. The Speed TR features specialized reinforcements, like a heel KippingKlip for efficient handstand pushups, a RopePro shank for durability, and a responsive propulsion plate enabling high-intensity transitions. Built for high speed, these shoes can handle it all, from EMOM to AMRAP.
bullet1: Monomesh and hotmelt overlay upper for breathable, WOD-tackling durability
bullet2: Low-cut design for freedom of motion and quicker transitions
bullet3: Ultra soft compression molded midsole for mitigating impact shock. Forefoot cradle with flat laces for high-end lateral and medial support
bullet4: Flared outsole and metasplit flex grooves for a super-stable lifting base
bullet5: KippingKlip TPU on the back heel allows for a smooth transition up and down the wall for those often programmed HSPUs
bullet6: RopePro shank for no-slide, tough protection during rope climbs
bullet7: Anti-friction collar and tongue lining to reduce moisture and heat build up

title: Reebok Floatride Run
description:
Run farther

From your first step to the last, Floatride long-distance running shoes feel light and responsive, letting you float through every stride. The one-piece Ultraknit upper is engineered in zones to offer support and breathable flexibility. Seamless construction and a 3D heel cradle limit irritation while locking in a comfortable fit.

Innovative cushioning

New Floatride pressure-set foam has a consistent cell structure that delivers the optimal mix of lightweight cushion and a responsive feel. Plus, the supportive foam rim centers and balances your foot throughout the gait cycle for a stabilized landing and launch.
color: Light Grey Heather / Medium Grey Heather / Solar Yellow / White / Black

bullet6: Weight: 7 oz (Women's Size 7), Drop: 8mm

title: Reebok Harmony Road
description:
Introducing our men’s Harmony Road long distance running shoes. With a performance-driven design and long-lasting cushioning, this sneaker offers both comfort and power. Mile after mile, the TriZone midsole delivers shock absorption in the heel as well as responsive propulsion in the forefoot, allowing for a fast transition and a smooth, balanced ride. Mesh in the upper adds breathability, while the seamless construction keeps irritation away.

Named the 2017 Runner’s World Best Debut for its performance-driven design and innovative KooshRide core technology. This sneaker provides cushioning, comfort and power that lasts mile after mile, even for your longest run. Runner’s World is a registered trademark of Rodale, Inc. All rights reserved.

title: Reebok x Artists For Humanity Classic Leather
description:
Reebok and Artists for Humanity are empowering youth through creativity and innovation.

Reebok has partnered with Boston-based Artists for Humanity (AFH), a pioneering program that enables social change for under-resourced youth. The aim of the partnership is to break down barriers for four young adults by providing paid creative work, affording them the opportunity to design limited edition sneakers via a unique mentorship program.

Reebok and AFH are proud to unveil three designs that are the result of this enterprising partnership.

Jonathan Vergara created a geographically-themed Reebok Classic Leather, reflecting both the brand’s birthplace as well as the current residence – Bolton, Northwest England and Canton, Massachusetts respectively. The hand-painted Atlantic Ocean-inspired vamp separates each continent, as represented by the contour lines on the heel and toe. The ‘1405’ code on each shoe represents the height of Bolton’s highest peak, Winter Hill. New England’s Mount Washington is called out by the ‘6289’ emboss on the heel.
bullet1: Leather upper for comfort and support
bullet2: Low-cut design for a sleek and sophisticated silhouette
bullet3: EVA midsole for cushion and shock absorption
bullet4: Upper design inspired by both our founding and headquarter cities
bullet5: Rubber outsole for traction
bullet6: Collaboration with Jonathan Vergara and Artists For Humanity

title: Reebok CrossFit Speed TR
description: Always be ready for your next rep. All-direction stability keeps your base of support solid, helping you exert maximum power and reach top speeds. The Speed TR features specialized reinforcements, like a heel KippingKlip for efficient handstand pushups, a RopePro shank for durability, and a responsive propulsion plate enabling high-intensity transitions. Built for high speed, these shoes can handle it all, from EMOM to AMRAP.
bullet1: Monomesh and hotmelt overlay upper for breathable, WOD-tackling durability
bullet2: Low-cut design for freedom of motion and quicker transitions
bullet3: Ultra soft compression molded midsole for mitigating impact shock. Forefoot cradle with flat laces for high-end lateral and medial support
bullet4: Flared outsole and metasplit flex grooves for a super-stable lifting base
bullet5: KippingKlip TPU on the back heel allows for a smooth transition up and down the wall for those often programmed HSPUs
bullet6: RopePro shank for no-slide, tough protection during rope climbs
bullet7: Anti-friction collar and tongue lining to reduce moisture and heat build up

title: Reebok x Artists For Humanity Workout Plus
description:
Reebok and Artists for Humanity are empowering youth through creativity and innovation.

Reebok has partnered with Boston-based Artists for Humanity (AFH), a pioneering program that enables social change for under-resourced youth. The aim of the partnership is to break down barriers for four young adults by providing paid creative work, affording them the opportunity to design limited edition sneakers via a unique mentorship program.

Reebok and AFH are proud to unveil three designs that are the result of this enterprising partnership.

Thornton ‘Sparticus’ Nguyen takes off on a flight of fancy by way of the Workout Plus – a rocket ship representing life’s journey through the turbulent mists of teenage years. The ‘Struggle Clouds’ of red, orange and pink portray a fiery launch, which settles into the deep navy sole like the mysterious expanse that awaits the accelerating spacecraft.
color: White / Medium Grey Heather / Solid Grey / Collegiate Navy / Chalk / Stone
bullet1: Suede upper is soft yet sturdy
bullet2: Low-cut design for freedom of motion at the ankles
bullet3: Die-cut EVA midsole absorbs shock and is lightweight
bullet4: All-over graphic
bullet5: High abrasion rubber outsole is durable
bullet6: Padded foam sockliner adds cushion

title: Reebok x Artists For Humanity Club C
description:
Reebok and Artists for Humanity are empowering youth through creativity and innovation.

Reebok has partnered with Boston-based Artists for Humanity (AFH), a pioneering program that enables social change for under-resourced youth. The aim of the partnership is to break down barriers for four young adults by providing paid creative work, affording them the opportunity to design limited edition sneakers via a unique mentorship program.

Reebok and AFH are proud to unveil three designs that are the result of this enterprising partnership.

Jonathan ‘Pineapple’ Tejeda and Kathleen ‘Kat’ Canola chose the 80s Club C tennis sneaker as their canvas. Sourcing their palette from William the Conqueror’s coat of arms, the designs feature red, blue and yellow elements complete with a Tudor Rose motif. The year ‘1066’ is stamped on the heel to represent the Battle of Hastings, which marked the beginning of the Norman Conquest of England.
color: Stucco / Lemon Squirt / Echo Blue / Scarlet / Gum
bullet1: Leather upper with a textured suede toecap for support and unique style

bullet4: Design created in collaboration with the youth of Boston's Artists for Humanity

title: Classic Leather MSP
description:
Designed using Reebok’s most iconic silhouette, the shoes feature split outsole blocking and sockliner graphics unique to each inspiration. Packaged in a well-worn “couch” box, the shoes are wrapped with specialty paper and come with a bag of sticky surprises.

The first design is a spin on a gooey PB&J sandwich and features an allover peanut butter colored nubuck upper with “jelly” lining and matching crystal gum and fuchsia iced outsole. Hidden on the sockliner is a caricature of the tasty lunchtime staple.

Next up is an all-white leather upper with a psychedelic two-toned raspberry slush inspired heel and lining. The blue and pink ice bottoms add an extra layer of chill when you need to cool down. Lurking on the sockliner is a friendly looking slush man.

The final shoe in the pack will make you crave a pan of sprinkle-covered brownies. The deliciously designed Classic Leather features a rich brown suede upper with rainbow lenticular heels. A chocolate crystal gum and rainbow-sprinkled outsole along with a brownie flying high on the sockliner is the perfect topping to this yummy treat.
bullet1: White: Leather upper. Khaki and brown: Suede upper.
bullet2: Low-cut design for an iconic silhouette
bullet3: Die-cut EVA midsole for lightweight cushioning and stability
bullet4: High abrasion rubber outsole for durability and traction
bullet5: Translucent split outsole
bullet6: Unique sockliner graphics
bullet7: Limited edition couch box, treats tissue, and treats sticker pack

title: Reebok Harmony Racer
description:
Pull to the front of the pack with our Harmony Racer. Made specifically for racing and track workouts, these running flats deliver a secure fit that won't weigh you down on your way to the finish line.

Cushion and Support

Loaded with competition-ready tech, this sneaker delivers big on cushion, traction, and support. The SmoothFuse upper secures your foot with a seamless fit that limits irritation, and lightweight mesh lets your feet breathe. The PwrZone Philosophy forefoot design promotes a more efficient stride, and a thin layer of rubber on the outsole maintains traction without adding weight.

Made for Racing

Not your average running shoe, our Harmony Racer is built on a narrower form for pure performance on the track or the road. The 3D LiteStrike midsole cushions each step and delivers a responsive feel, while the lacing system locks in your feet for a racing-specific fit.
color: Fire Spark / Solar Yellow / Brave Blue / White
bullet1: Best for: Competitive road racing, track workouts
bullet2: 3D LiteStrike midsole for cushion and responsive feel
bullet3: PwrZone Philosophy forefoot design promotes a more efficient stride
bullet4: Ultra thin layer of high abrasion rubber strategically placed on the outsole for targeted traction
bullet5: Materials: Seamless, SmoothFuse upper for a lightweight, irritation-free fit
bullet6: Midfoot support built into the lacing system for a secure, race-ready feel
bullet7: Weight: 6.0 oz (Unisex Size 9), Drop: 6mm

title: Shaq Attaq Modern
description:
To celebrate the 25th Anniversary of the Shaq Attaq, Reebok introduces a twist on the original, called the Shaq Attaq Modern.

The Shaq Attaq Modern was designed to be closer to the current trend of contemporary basketball sneakers. The leather is replaced with a woven mesh upper, which helps to reduce the overall weight of the shoe while keeping the structure of the original in place. The collar features a foam compound with net mesh overlay to provide padding around the ankles. Minimal stitching gives way to hot melt throughout while also providing dimension thru use of various technical lightweight synthetics on the upper.

Featured in an allover yellow spark color with sublimated black stripe down the middle, the Shaq Attaq Modern colorway was inspired by one of Shaq’s many nicknames.

title: Classic Leather MSP
description:
Designed using Reebok’s most iconic silhouette, the shoes feature split outsole blocking and sockliner graphics unique to each inspiration. Packaged in a well-worn “couch” box, the shoes are wrapped with specialty paper and come with a bag of sticky surprises.

The first design is a spin on a gooey PB&J sandwich and features an allover peanut butter colored nubuck upper with “jelly” lining and matching crystal gum and fuchsia iced outsole. Hidden on the sockliner is a caricature of the tasty lunchtime staple.

Next up is an all-white leather upper with a psychedelic two-toned raspberry slush inspired heel and lining. The blue and pink ice bottoms add an extra layer of chill when you need to cool down. Lurking on the sockliner is a friendly looking slush man.

The final shoe in the pack will make you crave a pan of sprinkle-covered brownies. The deliciously designed Classic Leather features a rich brown suede upper with rainbow lenticular heels. A chocolate crystal gum and rainbow-sprinkled outsole along with a brownie flying high on the sockliner is the perfect topping to this yummy treat.
color: Wild Khaki / Fierce Fuchsia / Classic White
bullet1: White: Leather upper. Khaki and brown: Suede upper.
bullet2: Low-cut design for an iconic silhouette
bullet3: Die-cut EVA midsole for lightweight cushioning and stability

title: Classic Leather
description:
Once a running shoe. Now a classic.

Turning heads since ’83, the Classic Leather stays true to its roots. Known as “The Classic”, it broke free from the pack by becoming the first running shoe to be made out of leather. Today, its heritage and timeless design still ring true as it delivers a casual, classic style that’s perfect for everyday wear.

One classic silhouette, countless options

The original white and black colorways set the standard for a classic style, and are easy-to-wear additions to your everyday outfits. For a bolder look, check out the full collection of Classic Leather shoes, featuring a variety of additional colors and materials. Or, design your own Classic Leather shoes to create a look that is unique to your classic style.
bullet1: Best for: everyday wear
bullet2: Soft leather upper for comfort, support, and an authentic heritage style
bullet3: Die-cut EVA midsole for lightweight cushioning
bullet4: Iconic silhouette featuring a low-cut design
bullet5: Padded foam sockliner for additional comfort
bullet6: High abrasion rubber outsole adds durability and traction

title: Custom Hayasu
description:
Design your own Hayasu shoes and let your style shine both in and out of the studio. Mix and match colors and graphics to add your own unique flair to this dependable yet stylish sneaker. Choose from splatter, bonestorm, fade, or multicolor designs.

As always, this shoe is engineered to support your feet through a full range of movements. Be cushioned from impacts thanks to our 3D Ultralite technology, and turn on a dime with the specialized TurnZone on the bottom of the shoes.

title: Custom FuryLite
description:
Step up your sole

Set your design apart from the rest with exclusive YourReebok midsole and outsole options. Paint your midsole with stripes, speckles, metallic silver, or even a glow in the dark color. Add a gum or ice bottom outsole to add a new twist to this classic shoe.

Choose your material

Pick from a variety of materials and graphics for your base. From mesh to chambray, customize your design with a material that shows off your style. Don’t forget graphics like camo print, polka dots, or studs.

title: Custom Classic Leather
description:
Let your style shine

Mix it up with exclusive midsole and outsole patterns like the split midsole or the arctic V outsole. Or, choose metallic, reflective, or glow in the dark leather to make your design really shine. Still not personalized enough for you? Add an embroidered name, number, or phrase to the back of your shoes.
